Later on,
Justice proved we were right.

273
00:16:54,613 --> 00:16:57,013
Our ruling freed Pilates
for all Argentina.

274
00:16:57,349 --> 00:17:00,580
Sandra went on with her business
and l married her.

275
00:17:00,953 --> 00:17:03,820
Gentlemen, the springs
are finely tuned.

276
00:17:03,989 --> 00:17:06,753
Be careful.

277
00:17:06,925 --> 00:17:09,587
Sandra, move over.
Can I help you, guys?

278
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:11,587
Hands up!

279
00:17:11,764 --> 00:17:14,028
l didn't charge her anything.

280
00:17:14,366 --> 00:17:17,028
But we went Dutch
on the wedding party.

281
00:17:17,369 --> 00:17:21,430
l never told her that Perelman
senior helped me with the trial.

282
00:17:21,607 --> 00:17:23,939
She still believes l pulled it off.

283
00:17:24,109 --> 00:17:25,940
l sometimes wonder if this lie

284
00:17:26,111 --> 00:17:28,306
would be grounds
for a marriage annulment.

285
00:17:35,454 --> 00:17:37,615
What is it, darling?
You want daddy?

286
00:17:37,790 --> 00:17:38,848
Daddy?

287
00:17:39,825 --> 00:17:42,794
I'm looking at him.
I'm right here.

288
00:17:42,961 --> 00:17:44,553
Now that we're a family

289
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:46,755
and have a son,
the picture's quite normal.

290
00:17:47,433 --> 00:17:49,901
it’s seems very natural.
But l know it isn't.

291
00:17:50,436 --> 00:17:53,564
Hooking up with Sandra
was some kind of a miracle.

292
00:17:54,206 --> 00:17:56,572
We never stopped decorating
since our honeymoon.

293
00:17:56,909 --> 00:17:59,469
And it seems to go on forever.

294
00:18:00,312 --> 00:18:02,576
Sandra wanted
to refurbish the house

295
00:18:02,748 --> 00:18:04,943
so she could work
and be a mother at the same time.

296
00:18:05,284 --> 00:18:06,751
We currently live together
with the painters,

297
00:18:06,919 --> 00:18:09,547
an ironworker
and the guy who does the floors.

298
00:18:09,721 --> 00:18:12,849
My son sometimes
calls one of them ''daddy''.

299
00:18:13,025 --> 00:18:15,186
-Are you painting, Gaston?
- It's blue.

300
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:17,794
No. The seat is blue.

301
00:18:17,963 --> 00:18:20,227
- What color is the wheel?
- This is blue.

302
00:18:20,399 --> 00:18:21,832
What color is the wheel?

303
00:18:22,634 --> 00:18:24,625
Beige 27 4?

304
00:18:24,803 --> 00:18:27,863
What is it? Poo?
He wants to poo.

305
00:18:28,507 --> 00:18:29,735
No, Sandra, not me, not poo.

306
00:18:29,908 --> 00:18:31,808
He wants to poo, Perelman!

307
00:18:32,044 --> 00:18:33,272
Again?
But he pooed this morning!

308
00:18:33,445 --> 00:18:36,937
it’s weird. in the mornings,
l run into gentlemen

309
00:18:37,116 --> 00:18:41,644
that come to my house.
My wife doesn't touch them much.

310
00:18:41,987 --> 00:18:43,420
There are also ladles,

311
00:18:43,589 --> 00:18:45,454
who try to make friends
with my wife.

312
00:18:47,259 --> 00:18:49,591
I’m not into Pilates.
it gives me vertigo.

313
00:18:50,162 --> 00:18:52,630
But sometimes,
when my wife and son are sleeping,

314
00:18:52,965 --> 00:18:55,934
l sit on the bed
and do some exercises.

315
00:18:56,101 --> 00:18:58,194
l think about how l became
a family man,

316
00:18:58,370 --> 00:19:00,998
and what it would have been like
if l had not.

317
00:19:01,406 --> 00:19:03,567
But l soon feel like going to bed.

318
00:19:11,283 --> 00:19:13,581
Perelman,
take off the suit to sleep.

319
00:19:14,153 --> 00:19:16,087
Then you complain it's all creased.

320
00:19:18,690 --> 00:19:20,590
Don't you remember
where Mom put it?

321
00:19:20,759 --> 00:19:23,023
She put it away! It's gone!

322
00:19:23,195 --> 00:19:25,254
What do you mean it's gone?

323
00:19:25,430 --> 00:19:26,362
It's not here.

324
00:19:26,532 --> 00:19:30,263
No, it's in the closet.
But where did she put it?

325
00:19:30,536 --> 00:19:33,664
- Where? Here?
- Over there.

326
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:36,338
- It's not here.
- It's there!

327
00:19:36,742 --> 00:19:37,936
- Here?
-Yes.

328
00:19:38,110 --> 00:19:41,011
There's nothing here.
I don't have all day, Gaston.

329
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:43,080
- Where?
- Down there.

330
00:19:43,749 --> 00:19:45,546
No, the other one.

331
00:19:46,385 --> 00:19:47,943
- Where?
- There it is.

332
00:19:48,120 --> 00:19:49,587
There's nothing here!

333
00:19:50,589 --> 00:19:53,023
- Tell me where it is.
- I don't know.

334
00:19:54,193 --> 00:19:56,058
Now, start breathing.

335
00:19:56,762 --> 00:19:59,959
Take the breath
into the stomach.

336
00:20:00,199 --> 00:20:01,564
That's right.

337
00:20:01,733 --> 00:20:05,499
Into the stomach,
right here...

338
00:20:05,671 --> 00:20:08,105
That's right...all in here.

339
00:20:08,340 --> 00:20:10,069
Now, hold the air in...

340
00:20:18,450 --> 00:20:19,747
You keep going.

341
00:20:22,154 --> 00:20:24,122
Nice job...right?

342
00:20:24,289 --> 00:20:25,688
You're going to be late.

343
00:20:26,024 --> 00:20:27,719
What does Gaston wear
for the kindergarten?

344
00:20:27,893 --> 00:20:30,919
- Did you buy the uniform?
- First drawer?

345
00:20:31,096 --> 00:20:33,064
- I checked the third drawer.
- First one.

346
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:34,494
Keep breathing folks!

347
00:20:34,666 --> 00:20:36,566
- Because if they don't...
- They'll die.

348
00:20:36,735 --> 00:20:38,794
- I've told this joke before?
- Repeatedly, over two years.

349
00:20:39,137 --> 00:20:41,571
I’ll just drop him there
and leave.

350
00:20:41,740 --> 00:20:43,674
- Or should I stay with him?
- He's already adapted.

351
00:20:43,842 --> 00:20:45,275
Then I’ll just drop him there.

352
00:20:48,513 --> 00:20:50,640
Watch it, it'll get dirty.

353
00:20:57,556 --> 00:20:59,285
What's this badge?

354
00:21:01,326 --> 00:21:03,055
What's this badge?

355
