Did they tell you what it meant?

356
00:21:10,502 --> 00:21:12,561
Did they tell you what it meant?

357
00:21:13,171 --> 00:21:15,696
I want more cards for the album.

358
00:21:15,874 --> 00:21:17,136
More?

359
00:21:48,273 --> 00:21:51,572
- Ponce, what happened?
- The masonry collapsed.

360
00:21:51,743 --> 00:21:53,210
Oases will be postponed
for thirty days.

361
00:21:53,378 --> 00:21:54,345
And the files?

362
00:21:54,513 --> 00:21:56,743
They're being submitted
to the Courts.

363
00:21:57,816 --> 00:22:00,216
Now you'll have time
to get a hair cut.

364
00:22:00,719 --> 00:22:02,118
Perelman, they won't Let you in.

365
00:22:02,287 --> 00:22:04,118
The structure collapsed
due to the weight of the files.

366
00:22:04,289 --> 00:22:05,256
The building has to close.

367
00:22:05,424 --> 00:22:07,221
All my things are inside.

368
00:22:07,392 --> 00:22:09,189
Did you try the cafeteria?

369
00:22:13,832 --> 00:22:16,824
What's up?
The building’s falling down on us.

370
00:22:17,169 --> 00:22:18,602
Are you going on holidays?

371
00:22:18,770 --> 00:22:21,739
No, no.
I want to take my things out

372
00:22:21,907 --> 00:22:23,568
before it all falls down.

373
00:22:23,742 --> 00:22:27,508
Can’t you Let me in?
Through there?

374
00:22:28,580 --> 00:22:29,740
That way.

375
00:22:30,716 --> 00:22:31,740
Bye.

376
00:22:32,250 --> 00:22:34,150
I’ll have another coffee later on.

377
00:22:41,893 --> 00:22:43,224
Good morning, Doctor.

378
00:23:20,532 --> 00:23:23,228
Treat the good man
with respect please.

379
00:23:56,935 --> 00:23:58,835
- Your wife knows already?
- Knows what?

380
00:23:59,004 --> 00:24:00,665
That you have a month's holiday.

381
00:24:00,839 --> 00:24:03,865
- No, why?
- Take advantage of it!

382
00:24:04,042 --> 00:24:06,533
You put on your suit,
goodbye my love,

383
00:24:06,711 --> 00:24:08,770
and have some time
for ''your things''.

384
00:24:08,947 --> 00:24:12,212
Darmidjian, I won't lie to my wife
for no reason.

385
00:24:12,384 --> 00:24:15,285
If I ever have ''a thing'',
then you can give me some advice.

386
00:24:18,590 --> 00:24:22,287
I’ll be needing you next week,
but to play ''the resented guy''.

387
00:24:22,461 --> 00:24:26,989
- I have this new course...
- No, I don't do that anymore.

388
00:24:27,332 --> 00:24:28,697
- ''No''?
- That was just a favor.

389
00:24:28,867 --> 00:24:30,334
What are you telling me?

390
00:24:30,502 --> 00:24:34,438
People really buy it.
They are genuinely moved.

391
00:24:35,373 --> 00:24:38,035
I mean it! Pedagogically,
it's really something...

392
00:24:38,376 --> 00:24:40,469
The professors take it
as an example.

393
00:24:40,645 --> 00:24:42,840
- My colleagues tease me.
- They don't!

394
00:24:57,996 --> 00:25:02,456
