and ''we-can-make-it''

396
00:25:05,103 --> 00:25:07,799
means we really want him to win.

397
00:25:07,973 --> 00:25:08,997
It's the spirit of the turf.

398
00:25:09,341 --> 00:25:11,502
O'mon-Garcllazo-we-can-make-it!

399
00:25:21,353 --> 00:25:22,843
Which horse did you bet on?

400
00:25:23,388 --> 00:25:24,912
Garcllazo's, all of it.

401
00:25:29,327 --> 00:25:30,419
It's over.

402
00:25:33,832 --> 00:25:37,063
-Are you seeing your kids?
- Yes, yes...

403
00:25:38,336 --> 00:25:41,669
Everything is OK.
Half an hour a day belongs to them.

404
00:25:42,541 --> 00:25:44,634
In that sense,
the pediatrician is right:

405
00:25:44,809 --> 00:25:46,834
nothing beats quality time.

406
00:25:51,516 --> 00:25:52,483
And this one?

407
00:25:52,651 --> 00:25:54,676
Forget it.
It's pure Italian Jacquard.

408
00:26:00,191 --> 00:26:01,590
Is it a gift?

409
00:26:02,327 --> 00:26:03,351
Yes.

410
00:26:22,948 --> 00:26:26,782
...and that has more to do
with our ambitions as Lawyers,

411
00:26:26,952 --> 00:26:29,420
with our dreams, if you will.

412
00:26:29,588 --> 00:26:31,146
Dreams
in two senses of the word.

413
00:26:31,323 --> 00:26:34,815
On the one side,
there's the Lawyer I dream to be.

414
00:26:34,993 --> 00:26:36,517
I might want to be
a successful Lawyer

415
00:26:36,695 --> 00:26:40,426
and I don't care about
the amount of truth I deal in.

416
00:26:40,599 --> 00:26:44,160
But, perhaps,
you're interested in the truth.

417
00:26:44,336 --> 00:26:47,737
It's the main reason,
the essence of your calling.

418
00:27:52,637 --> 00:27:53,831
Sandra...

419
00:27:54,572 --> 00:27:57,666
There's a problem
in the building...

420
00:27:58,276 --> 00:28:00,801
No, it's just for today,
something with the water.

421
00:28:00,979 --> 00:28:02,469
No big deal.

422
00:28:03,815 --> 00:28:05,874
They think it's just for today.

423
00:28:06,051 --> 00:28:10,454
I thought of picking up Gaston
from the kindergarten.

424
00:28:10,889 --> 00:28:13,323
And taking him to the Zoo...

425
00:28:14,025 --> 00:28:16,391
What do you mean he's having
swimming Lessons?

426
00:28:17,028 --> 00:28:21,431
Why teach him that now?
He's two and a half years old!

427
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:25,465
Well, I can teach him to swim
when he turns thirteen.

428
00:28:26,337 --> 00:28:28,328
It's just for today.
He can skip swimming.

429
00:28:28,707 --> 00:28:30,607
OK, fine... bye, sweetheart.

430
00:28:33,344 --> 00:28:36,279
- Who wants the piggy?
- I want it!

431
00:28:36,614 --> 00:28:37,672
Here it is.

432
00:28:39,050 --> 00:28:40,381
It's so good you came
to pick him up.

433
00:28:40,552 --> 00:28:43,453
Kids Like it when daddy
comes to pick them up.

434
00:28:44,055 --> 00:28:45,522
This belongs to him,

435
00:28:45,690 --> 00:28:48,454
