01:28:22,096 --> 01:28:23,085
Norita.

1234
01:28:28,636 --> 01:28:31,605
Well, thanks a lot.
You shouldn't have bothered.

1235
01:28:31,773 --> 01:28:33,297
No bother at all.

1236
01:28:33,741 --> 01:28:35,368
Here you have the keys.

1237
01:28:35,543 --> 01:28:36,737
I've put everything in boxes.

1238
01:28:36,911 --> 01:28:39,106
The cleaning lady
is coming tomorrow.

1239
01:28:39,447 --> 01:28:41,813
What will you do with...?
Will you rent it out?

1240
01:28:41,983 --> 01:28:44,975
No, for the time being,
I’ll Leave things as they are.

1241
01:28:46,688 --> 01:28:48,986
Tell me, Norita,
have you made any plans yet?

1242
01:28:49,157 --> 01:28:51,091
I mean
for the next few months.

1243
01:28:52,527 --> 01:28:55,758
The truth is
I'm still trying to figure it out.

1244
01:28:55,930 --> 01:29:00,492
I'm telling you because
there's a vacancy here.

1245
01:29:00,802 --> 01:29:03,396
Defense Lawyer's assistant.

1246
01:29:03,571 --> 01:29:05,698
I happen
to be the Defense Lawyer.

1247
01:29:05,873 --> 01:29:08,933
So I guess
I'd Like you to work with me.

1248
01:29:09,177 --> 01:29:11,702
What would
the working hours be?

1249
01:29:12,580 --> 01:29:14,844
Because I'm getting on a bit.

1250
01:29:15,016 --> 01:29:18,349
There are things I can't do.
I'm telling you in advance.

1251
01:29:18,653 --> 01:29:19,620
That's the plain truth.

1252
01:29:19,787 --> 01:29:23,587
We start at 8:30am
and Leave at 2pm.

1253
01:29:23,958 --> 01:29:25,892
From 8:30 to 2:00.

1254
01:29:26,794 --> 01:29:30,992
I haven't worked mornings
in so many years...

1255
01:29:31,165 --> 01:29:33,725
But I can always
give it a try, right?

1256
01:29:34,068 --> 01:29:36,969
- I don't know.
- The truth is, I'd Love to.

1257
01:29:37,171 --> 01:29:38,798
Take your time
and think about it.

1258
01:29:38,973 --> 01:29:40,907
I don't need
an answer right now.

1259
01:29:41,642 --> 01:29:44,133
I think it'd be fun
because I've never done it before.

1260
01:29:49,217 --> 01:29:50,411
And the kids?

1261
01:29:52,687 --> 01:29:53,915
Behind the stage, sweetheart.

1262
01:29:54,088 --> 01:29:55,146
- Yes, but...
- Enjoy it...

1263
01:30:43,237 --> 01:30:44,795
Look at Gaston.

1264
01:31:19,774 --> 01:31:21,139
What's he saying?

1265
01:31:22,143 --> 01:31:24,043
That he's wearing
a suit and a tale, Like you.

1266
01:31:24,212 --> 01:31:25,201
You have a suit Like daddy?

1267
01:31:51,372 --> 01:31:53,738
Remember when he was a baby?

1268
01:31:54,709 --> 01:31:56,643
You were worried 'cause
he didn't Look Like you.

1269
01:31:56,811 --> 01:31:58,870
Now, with the suit,
he does Look Like you.

1270
01:32:00,348 --> 01:32:04,785
But Let’s not insist on it.
Better Leave him Like he is now.

1271
01:32:06,120 --> 01:32:09,112
He can Look Like his father
whenever he wants... if he wants.

1272
01:32:12,326 --> 01:32:13,850
What's the rush?

1273
01:32:17,298 --> 01:32:18,822
Why hurry?

